HEADWORD: Spilliard fishing
<hw>Spil"liard
fish`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <def>A system or method of fishing
by means of a number of hooks set on snoods all on one line; -- in North
America, called <altname>trawl fishing</altname>,
<altname>bultow</altname>, or <altname>bultow fishing</altname>, and
<altname>long-line fishing</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spillikin</ent>⟦br⟧
